Currently in the constructor the default is `trace=None` which ends up turning off the sampling of the spans to 0. 

Should this perhaps be `trace=True` by default?  If the `opentracing.tracer` is not initialized, then `trace=True` still results in no tracing, so it feels like an unnecessary switch, only for very special cases like Hyperbahn requests.

